Vice President Mike Pence addressed the Annual National Conservative Student Conference, praising the Young America's Foundation (YAF) for its contributions to the conservative movement. He commended YAF President Ron Robinson and announced that Governor Scott Walker would be taking over the organization. Pence also brought greetings from President Donald Trump and emphasized the importance of conservative values and principles. He highlighted the accomplishments of the Trump administration, such as tax cuts, deregulation, and job creation, as well as their focus on national defense and appointing conservative judges. Pence warned against the rise of socialism in the Democratic Party and called on the young conservatives to be leaders and defenders of freedom. He encouraged them to stay engaged, study the foundations of American greatness, and have faith in the American people and in God.